  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1636546023982-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1636546023982-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1636546023982-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1636546023982-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1636546023982-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges, then peel and finely dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1636546028857-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1636546028857-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1636546028857-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1636546028857-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1636546028857-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the onion is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1636546031636-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1636546031636-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1636546031636-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1636546031636-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1636546031636-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is softening, deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1636546034486-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1636546034486-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1636546034486-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1636546034486-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1636546034486-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is beginning to soften, add your <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> pepper strips</strong>, <strong>drained black beans</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix together until everything is coated in the spices</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1636546037869-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1636546037869-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1636546037869-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1636546037869-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1636546037869-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> with 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [275ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the sweet potato has softened and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>smoky sweet potato and black bean stew</strong></p><p>Whilst the stew is cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly and chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1636546040289-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1636546040289-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1636546040289-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1636546040289-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1636546040289-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut your <strong>orange[s]</strong> in half, then roughly chop half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>diced onion</strong>,<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and the <strong>chopped orange </strong>to a bowl with the juice of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>orange</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chilli-orange salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1636546043476-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1636546043476-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1636546043476-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1636546043476-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1636546043476-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>brown rice</strong> with the <strong>smoky sweet potato and black bean stew </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with the <strong>chilli-orange salsa</strong> and a dollop of your <strong>natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining chopped coriander </strong>over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
